{"actual_usd":0.12415000000000001,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":179,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24293,"reply":"\"No... not less God.\" *I rub a thumb along a dry streak of clay on my apron, thinking how often people mistake order for inferiority.* \"Greater can mean place, sending, or role without meaning lesser in nature. A king can send his son into the mud on purpose; the mud doesn't make him less royal.\"\n\n*I glance toward the window where the morning light keeps shifting under the clouds.* \"As I'd say it plain: the Father, the Son, and the Spirit aren't stacked like rungs on a ladder of divinity. If Jesus is speaking from his lived place as the one sent—humbling himself, obeying, suffering—then 'the Father is greater than I' tells you something true about that relation, not that he's a smaller god. And the Spirit—no, not less either. Same God, not a dimmer portion.\"","rolling_24h_usd":35.721980000000016,"run_id":"4bbb6749-29ee-4944-9cdc-31dbecb8fdd1"}
